tafsir[7]{c,v,t}:
  42,45,"The following are the arguments by which the doctrine of parenthood has been refuted:"
  42,46,"For explanation, see (Surah Ibrahim, Ayat 19); (Surah An-Nahl, Ayat 3); (Surah Al-Ankabut, Ayat 44), and the E.Ns thereof."
  42,47,"That is, He is All-Mighty: if He wills to punish you, no power can resist Him. But it is His kindness that He does not seize you forthwith in spite of your arrogant and insolent behavior, but He goes on giving you respite after respite. Here, Allah's making no haste in seizing people in punishment and His giving them respite has been called forgiveness."
  42,48,"This does not mean that first He created the human beings from Adam and then created his wife, Eve. But here, instead of the chronological order, there is the order of presentation, examples of which are found in every language. For instance, we say, “Whatever you did today is known to me, and whatever you did yesterday is also in my knowledge.” This cannot mean that what happened yesterday has happened after today."
  42,49,"That is, the camel, cow, sheep and goat, whose four males and four females together make eight heads of cattle."
  42,50,"The three dark veils are: the belly, the womb and the caul or membrane enclosing the fetus."
  42,51,"“Your Lord”: your Master, Ruler and Providence."